### CSS Pseudo-Classes

A **pseudo-class** defines a special state of an element.

---

### Syntax

```css
selector:pseudo-class {
  property: value;
}
```

---

### Interactive Pseudo-Classes

| Pseudo-Class | When It Applies |
|-------------|----------------|
| `:hover` | Mouse is over the element |
| `:active` | Element is being clicked |
| `:focus` | Element has keyboard focus |
| `:visited` | Link has been visited |
| `:link` | Unvisited link |
| `:target` | Element is the URL target |

```css
a:hover {
  color: red;
}

input:focus {
  border-color: blue;
  outline: none;
}

button:active {
  transform: scale(0.98);
}
```

---

### Structural Pseudo-Classes

| Pseudo-Class | Selects |
|-------------|---------|
| `:first-child` | First child of parent |
| `:last-child` | Last child of parent |
| `:nth-child(n)` | Nth child (1-indexed) |
| `:nth-last-child(n)` | Nth from end |
| `:first-of-type` | First of its type |
| `:last-of-type` | Last of its type |
| `:only-child` | Only child of parent |
| `:empty` | Elements with no children |

```css
/* Odd rows */
tr:nth-child(odd) {
  background: #f0f0f0;
}

/* Every 3rd element */
li:nth-child(3n) {
  color: red;
}
```

---

### Input Pseudo-Classes

```css
input:checked { outline: 2px solid blue; }
input:disabled { opacity: 0.5; }
input:required { border-color: orange; }
input:valid { border-color: green; }
input:invalid { border-color: red; }
```

---

> **Pro Tip:** Use `:nth-child(odd)` and `:nth-child(even)` for alternating row colors in tables.
